tool. And in this talk, I'm going to show you how you can use it with Reticulate, which

00:06:46.920 --> 00:06:55.359
is an R Python bridge where you can interchange data functions and objects between the two

00:06:55.359 --> 00:07:07.399
runtimes. So what? So the point here is that using Pandera in your Python and R stacks

00:07:07.399 --> 00:07:12.440
gets you a single source of truth for your schemas, data documentation as code for you

00:07:12.440 --> 00:07:18.320
and your team to look at, and runtime data frame schema enforcers. So you can spend less

00:07:18.320 --> 00:07:24.160
time worrying about the correctness of your data and more time analyzing, visualizing,

00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:27.720
and modeling them.

00:07:27.720 --> 00:07:33.600
So in the rest of this talk, I'm going to take you through a mini data validation journey,

00:07:33.600 --> 00:07:40.480
starting with defining our goal. So say we have a toy data set here of transactions consisting

